  "prompt": "How can I add more topics here in Quora?",
  "response": "To add more topics on Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Log in to Quora**: Make sure you are logged into your Quora account.\n\n2. **Search for a Topic**: Use the search bar at the top of the page to see if the topic you want to add already exists. Quora has a wide range of topics, so it's a good idea to check if the topic is already covered.\n\n3. **Create a New Topic**: If the topic doesn\u2019t exist, you might have the option to create it. However, note that creating new topics on Quora is usually limited to experienced users or those with certain privileges.\n\n4. **Follow Topics**: If you find existing topics related to your interests, click on them and then select \"Follow\" to add them to your feed. This will enhance your Quora experience by tailoring the content you see.\n\n5. **Engage with the Community**: Before creating new topics, engage with the community by asking and answering questions. This interaction might increase your profile's credibility and may help you get the ability to create new topics over time.\n\n6. **Suggest Edits**: On occasion, you might find a topic that is somewhat related but could use further refinement. You can suggest edits to existing topics if you believe they need adjustments.\n\nRemember, Quora's moderation system is designed to prevent spam and maintain quality, so new topics are often subject to review before they become available. Engaging positively within the platform and building a good standing can eventually give you more flexibility in creating and managing topics.",
